- 'visible wealth' refers to the transaction income;
- 'financial shadows' and 'murky waters' metaphorically describe financial transactions involving taxes;
- 'state’s claims' represents tax owed;
- 'intricate dance' symbolizes the interaction and calculation between income, tax, and overall financial transactions.

- 'Gardeners nurturing their financial gardens' represents clients who manage their financial transactions;
- 'Blooms (income)' refers to the income recorded in transactions;
- 'Golden threshold of $10,000' is the tax on income exceeding $10,000;
- 'Average sun (income) and shadow (expense)' symbolizes the average income and average expense;
- 'Average sun (income) outshines their shadow (expense)' means the average income is higher than the average expense.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT client_id) AS unique_client_count
FROM financial_transactions
WHERE strftime('%Y', transaction_date) BETWEEN '2017' AND '2018';

SELECT SUM(total_amount)
FROM client_invoices
WHERE status = 'paid';

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT b.client_id) AS unique_client_count
FROM bank_accounts b
WHERE b.bank_name = 'Bank of America';

SELECT client_id, account_number, account_type, bank_name, routing_number
FROM bank_accounts
WHERE account_type = 'savings';
